'''Guarani Braille''' is the [[braille]] alphabet of the [[Paraguayan Guarani language]].<ref>UNESCO (2013) [http://www.pharmabraille.com/LiteratureRetrieve.aspx?ID=122064 World Braille Usage], 3rd edition.</ref> Letter assignments are those of [[Spanish Braille]] (except for the accented vowels): that is, the [[basic braille alphabet]] plus {{bc|12456}} for ''[[ñ]]''. An additional letter, {{bc|25}}, is used for [[glottal stop]], written as an apostrophe in the [[Guarani alphabet|Guarani print alphabet]]. Print digraphs such as ''ch'' and ''rr'' are digraphs in braille as well. In addition, the tilde in print is written as the letter {{bc|156}} in braille, and comes before the letter it appears on in print. Thus the Guarani letters outside the [[ISO basic Latin alphabet|basic Latin alphabet]] are:
